li.p: Maximum capacitive loading permitted for SRAM memory to support 55 ns access time is 30 pf.
Maximum capacitive loading permitted for SRAM memory to support 70 ns access time is 100 pf.
Maximum capacitive loading permitted for flash memory to support 55 ns and 70 ns access time is 30 pf.
Maximum capacitive loading permitted for flash memory to support 120 ns access time is 100 pf.
T_RC[7:0] and T_BTA[7:0] are defined in the Static Timing Set Register.
